Startled, Winter blasted a gale of ice, and Summer unleashed a torrent of heat. The wall of absolute zero and the wave of scorching sun rushed toward a collision that promised a terrestrial disaster. Kaelo, unafraid, stood on his hind legs to intercept the climates. He caught the frost on his thick coat and the fire on his broad chest.

The thermal shock didn't destroy him; instead, his enduring strength tempered the extremes into a cycle. The unchanging twilight shattered, giving way to the budding spring and the falling leaf. Kaelo, now the Spirit of Seasons, slumbers and wakes eternally, proving that cold and heat, when bridged by endurance, create the rhythm of life.

